WEBVTT

00:03:59.855 --> 00:04:02.355
You don't know what future you
is going to be like.

00:04:02.379 --> 00:04:04.990
AG: Maria Konnikova knows this well.

00:04:05.014 --> 00:04:07.831
The seeds for her career
were planted pretty early,

00:04:07.855 --> 00:04:10.617
tracing back to when she was
a toddler in Moscow.

00:04:10.641 --> 00:04:11.895
MK: God, I hate saying it,

00:04:11.919 --> 00:04:15.293
but behind the Iron Curtain --
this was before the Berlin Wall fell --

00:04:15.317 --> 00:04:19.505
and my parents were able
to leave the Soviet Union

00:04:19.529 --> 00:04:20.822
because we were Jewish.

00:04:20.846 --> 00:04:22.642
So we did what a lot of people did,

00:04:22.666 --> 00:04:25.212
and applied for political asylum
to the United States.

00:04:25.236 --> 00:04:29.537
And this was probably the only time
in the history of the world

00:04:29.561 --> 00:04:33.419
where people would forge their passports,
sometimes, to say that they were Jewish,